text: Medway (commonly called the Medway Towns) is a large urban area in North Kent. It is made up of 5 towns: Strood, Rochester, Chatham, Gillingham and Rainham. It is named after the River Medway. As of 2019 it has 278,016 people. == References == == Other websites == * Medway Council * Archive Images * Detailed history of the Medway Towns * Chatham's World Heritage Site application * Medway's UK City of Culture 2025 bid Category:Medway
